title: Junior Web Automation Developer
description:

Our mission is to revolutionize human\\-machine collaboration by building AI that truly understands and augments individual workflows, helping users reclaim valuable time and enhance productivity. Join us on this transformative journey to unlock the full potential of agentic superintelligence and experience AI that works for you.

 Lyzn AI is building automation agents that power our marketplace. You‚Äôll write Go/JS/TS services that

 treats GitHub like a lab, and loves shipping scrappy, clever solutions. Indie hacker energy

**What You‚Äôll Do** 




 ‚óè Automate web flows (forms, logins, clicks, downloads, file handling).

**Must\\-Haves‚õ≥Ô∏è**

**Nice\\-to\\-Haves:üå±** 




 ‚óè Solid Go fundamentals (goroutines, channels, JSON, HTTP).

**Compensation \\& Growth** 




 ‚óè ‚Çπ25,000‚Äì‚Çπ40,000 per month.

* Mail your resume and GitHub profile to shivacharan@lyzn.ai

title: Risk & Compliance - AI, Automation and Innovation Specialist
description:
As a content\\-driven technology company, Thomson Reuters operates in a uniquely complex and regulated environment. We are reimagining how we manage risk and compliance, moving away from traditional processes and toward intelligent, automated systems.
   

  

 This is a unique opportunity to be a foundational engineer within the risk and compliance team. We are looking for a hands\\-on builder who is passionate about using AI and automation to solve complex problems. You will not be just maintaining systems or checking boxes; you will be architecting and creating the core tools that will help our entire organization innovate more safely and effectively. Your work will have a direct and visible impact on the business.
   

  

**About the Role:**
* Build AI\\-Powered Solutions:‚ÄØDesign, code, and deploy intelligent workflows and autonomous agents to automate risk detection and analysis. You'll work with technologies like LLMs to turn unstructured data (eg. regulatory documents) into actionable insights.
* Solve Business Problems with Code:‚ÄØCollaborate directly with risk and compliance experts to understand their core processes and challenges, then design and build the end\\-to\\-end technical solutions that reimagine and solve them.
* Drive Innovation and Experimentation:‚ÄØProactively explore, prototype, and implement cutting\\-edge technologies. You'll have the autonomy to experiment with the latest AI frameworks and tools to find novel solutions to our business challenges.
* Own and Scale Your Work:‚ÄØTake full ownership of your projects, from the initial concept and architecture through to deployment and continuous improvement, ensuring your solutions are scalable and robust.


**About You:**
 We are looking for a curious problem\\-solver who is eager to build. A strong foundation in software development is essential. Your hands\\-on experience and relevant projects in AI/ML are just as important to us as your formal professional history.
   

  

**Required Skills \\& Experience:**
* Hands\\-on Development:‚ÄØProficiency in a modern programming language like Python or Java, with experience building and shipping applications or automation scripts with 10\\+ years of experience.
* AI \\& Machine Learning Interest:‚ÄØDemonstrable experience or a strong personal interest in AI/ML. You've likely experimented with LLMs, AI agents, or related frameworks (either professionally or on personal projects).
* Problem\\-Solving Mindset:‚ÄØYou are an analytical thinker who can break down complex, ambiguous problems into manageable technical steps.
* Strong Communication:‚ÄØYou can clearly explain complex technical concepts to both technical and non\\-technical partners.
* Analytical Thinking:‚ÄØStrong problem\\-solving skills with the ability to analyse complex systems and processes.
* Communication:‚ÄØExcellent verbal and written communication skills, capable of conveying complex technical concepts to non\\-technical stakeholders.
* Leadership:‚ÄØProven ability to take initiative and drive initiatives from concept to implementation.
* Adaptability:‚ÄØComfortable working in a fast\\-paced, evolving environment with the flexibility to adapt to changing priorities.


**What‚Äôs in it For You?**
* Hybrid Work Model: We‚Äôve adopted a flexible hybrid working environment (2\\-3 days a week in the office depending on the role) for our office\\-based roles while delivering a seamless experience that is digitally and physically connected.
* Flexibility \\& Work\\-Life Balance: Flex My Way is a set of supportive workplace policies designed to help manage personal and professional responsibilities, whether caring for family, giving back to the community, or finding time to refresh and reset. This builds upon our flexible work arrangements, including work from anywhere for up to 8 weeks per year, empowering employees to achieve a better work\\-life balance.
* Career Development and Growth: By fostering a culture of continuous learning and skill development, we prepare our talent to tackle tomorrow‚Äôs challenges and deliver real\\-world solutions. Our Grow My Way programming and skills\\-first approach ensures you have the tools and knowledge to grow, lead, and thrive in an AI\\-enabled future.
